SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 575
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the West Tennessee
Annual Conference of the African Methodist
Episcopal Church on the occasion of its 151st
Session.
WHEREAS, the churches of our nation have been an integral part of our history as a
people and have had an unparalleled impact in forming and maintaining a stable and just
society; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should recognize those venerable religious
institutions that, through their unflagging capacity for love, dedication of spirit, and faith in God,
strive to enrich the lives of people in their communities; and
WHEREAS, the West Tennessee Annual Conference of the African Methodist Episcopal
(AME) Church convened its 151st Session in Memphis, from October 7-11, 2025; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 Session was hosted by St. James African Methodist Episcopal
Church, located at 600 North Fourth Street in Memphis, where Reverend Dr. Walter R. Henry
faithfully serves as pastor; and
WHEREAS, building upon the strong foundation of African Methodism, more than 300
ministers, clergy, and lay delegates from across West Tennessee participated in worship,
business, and service that continued the AME Church's longstanding commitment to minister to
the social, spiritual, and physical development of all people; and
WHEREAS, in commemoration of the 151st Session of the West Tennessee Annual
Conference of the African Methodist Episcopal (AME) Church, we wish to specially recognize
the Church's leadership, pastors, and laity for their exemplary service to their fellow Christians
and to the good people of Tennessee; now, therefore,
SJR0575
010754
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and commend the West Tennessee
Annual Conference of the African Methodist Episcopal Church on the occasion of its 151st
Session and extend to the Church's ministers, clergy, and lay delegates our best wishes for
continued success and happiness in the years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
